description:
A dark evil has emerged from the depths of space, in search of a power that would make them gods. They had captured the Boy Guardian of our universe, using the little remaining power he had the Boy Guardian brings together ten unlikely heroes to save our universe!

These Guardians ten have been tasked to protect the ultimate power!

But first they must learn to be a team, 10 strangers thrown together, a diverse mix of talents and personalities. This epic story takes you on a wild action packed adventure that will touch all of your emotions as it builds up to the climatic finish!

A teacher at an exclusive school for the children of United Nations delegates is found brutally tortured and murdered.

The Tactical, Operational Response and Control Headquarters (TORCH) sends in one of their best agents, Kathryn Monroe, to investigate.

Kathryn must use all her skills as an investigator as she puts herself in the firing line to uncover the murderer... and their dark secret.

Illuminia: The Darkshe

A world, worlds away, where the line between the material and spiritual realms shifts like sands in the wind, she is the Guardian of the Light against the dark demonic world that exists below men's feet. Chosen and trained by the priests of the High Order of the Light, Parah V'Tel Illuminia is one of a handful of mortals who possess the great natural gifts of a LightBringer: Flight, Magic, and

Heightened Sensory Perception. Though young, her powers are extraordinary, even among her peers. And though exemplary in tracking and destroying demons,

she is wracked with doubt about her mission.
name: The Darkshe

description:
The Truth makes liars of us all. The Truth will kill you, or get you killed. It'll steal your marriage and your daughter's love. The Truth will get you shot and left for dead in the desert...

So when a woman tells you she woke up in a bathtub full of blood and ice with stitches in her belly that she can't explain, you'll know it's the Truth because nothing else smells or feels or hurts that bad - and you'll fall for it all over again, even though you know you were lucky before and it'll burn you even worse this time.

This, then, is the story of The Immaculate Abortion of Dina Leigh - and I'm daring you to call me a liar...

volume.name: The Immaculate Abortion of Dina Leigh

description: Sisters Zoe and Sydney make a new friend with the help of their magical television set.

Absurd Pomp

Forsleuth! When the Queen goes missing, it's up to Bard and Page to track her down. The future of literature lies in the balance!

Featuring art from superstar artists Erica Henderson (Squirrel Girl/Jughead), Cara McGee (Over The Garden Wall), James Callahan (The Auteur), and Aaron Conley (Sabertooth Swordsman), with a cover by Dave Kloc and pin-ups from Sina Grace, Bobby Rubio and Ashlyn Anstee.
A guide leads two explorers to an ancient, massive underground cave. What they find there will be a lesson in humility.
Petrichor is the third story in the series of vignettes in a shared universe. There will be at least 6 of such stories published over the next 2-3 years, each with a different artist.

In a bright flash of light, every superpowered hero and villain on the planet became POWERLESS! Seven years later, most heroes have tried to move on with their lives, but Justin Light (the hero once known as Helios) is determined to regain his life of adventure and glory, no matter what the cost.

Teenager Amy Berg is taken from her guardian and forced by the government to attend the Center for Intuitive Studies for her education. A rebellious outcast, she knows that life is going to get worse than she could even imagine. Amy, like the others there, seems to have special abilities and the CIS wants to train the students in order to help society. Well, that's what the brochures say...

Haruka is a delinquent student still struggling to graduate from high school after failing his exams before. The solution, according to Haruka's congressman father? Hire someone to make sure he gets into university by following him around and nagging him, of course! Shidou is supposed to be Haruka's "secretary" (read: babysitter), there to encourage him to pass his exams this time, but when Haruka only agrees to graduate on the condition that Shidou become his boyfriend... what's a megane character to do?! Second Honey follows the rather unconventional relationship between the older, bespectacled professional Shidou and Haruka, the flippant student more interested in messing with Shidou and pissing off his father than actually pursuing his studies. Is Haruka just playing around, or is there really something there? Is this sweet feeling like real honey, or just a cheap imitation? Sometimes, even Haruka doesn't know.

Contents

  • Second Honey #1 09.2008 first time catalog
  • Second Honey #2 11.2008 love triangle catalog
  • Second Honey #3 01.2009 social difference catalog
  • Second Honey Last Story 11.2008 seme x seme catalog
  • Sound of Blue Footsteps 11.2007 youth catalog
  • 365th Day's Miracle First Half 01.2008 rival catalog
  • 365th Day's Miracle Second Half 03.2008 career catalog
  • Second Honey ~Graduation~ miracle until the kiss
name: Vol. 1

description: From New York Times-bestselling author Nancy Holder comes this collection that features a brand new Domino Lady comic story, a brand new Holmes/Domino illustrated prose story, a Holmes/Domino Lady prose story with new illustrations, and reprints Sherlock Holmes/Domino Lady issues#1-2, and The Holmes Holiday Special story!
name: TPB

description: From the pages of the acclaimed fantasy series rides Sir Apropos of Nothing, a cynical knight who thinks far less of the art of chivalry than he does the art of raking in gold. Written by the novel series' creator, the man in black may be fleeing across the desert, but Apropos is riding across the desert on a horse with no name, seeking out a buried treasure, and running afoul of an acclaimed and slightly familiar tower that's somewhat dark.
name: GN

volume.name: Sir Apropos of Nothing: Gypsies, Vamps, And Thieves

description:
When the two closest friends of demon hunter Niall Robertson are found dead in a hotel room, he feels no grief--only rage and a desire for vengeance.

In order to know where to focus his anger and where to take his revenge, Niall invokes a grisly blood magic--but what he discovers when he uses it isn't what he wants to hear.

See No Evil finds a man in desperate need of information and whose ways of getting it may not lead to the truth he seeks.

volume.name: Split Lip Presents: See No Evil

description:
Ever wondered who makes your clothes? Who sells them? How much they get paid? How the fashion and sex industries are intertwined?

Threadbare draws the connections between the international sex and garment trades and human trafficking in a beautifully illustrated comics series. Anne Elizabeth Moore, in reports illustrated by top-notch comics creators, pulls at the threads of gender, labor, and cultural production to paint a concerning picture of a human rights in a globalized world. Moore's reporting, illustrated by members of the Ladydrawers Comics Collective, takes the reader from the sweatshops of Cambodia to the traditional ateliers of Vienna, from the life of a globetrotting supermodel to the warehouses of large clothing retailers, from the secondhand clothing industry to the politics of the sex trade. With thoughtful illustrations of women's stories across the sex and garment supply chain, this book offers a practical guide to a growing problem few truly understand.

Featuring the work of Leela Corman, Julia Gfrörer, Simon Häussle, Delia Jean, Ellen Lindner, and Melissa Mendes.

Note: The digital edition (5/11/2016) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: TPB

description: In a gritty, star-spanning future, where mankind has colonized planets throughout the galaxy, former Confederation Commander Jon T. Munro was serving a life sentence for a war crime he was forced to commit. When a prison break runs amok, however, he seizes the opportunity to escape with a ragtag team of cons to form a small crew of pirates with one goal in mind: vengeful justice. And the first step in their plan is to steal the battle cruiser he once commanded, a state-of-the-art warship they call "The Jolly Roger".
Chapter 2 of ABOVE THE CLOUDS, a story of two intertwining worlds--the adventures of a hero who must save a dying world, and a girl who must convince an author to finish what he has started.
name: Chapter 2

description:
Space Crud

A vicious alien space crud is taking over the city of Pickleton and it's up to Billy and his crew to clean this mess up.
name: Space Crud

volume.name: The Adventures of a 4th Grade Space Captain

description: Bayani and Tala didn't expect to actually FIND a monstrous guardian at the top of Mt. Makiling but now that they have, it's a battle of wits against the roaring fire and rage of the Lalahan! If the kids can rescue the Moon's daughter, Amparo, they have some hope of discovering where they have to go next! For readers of all ages.
name: And the Witch of the Mountain

description: While Germany prepares for an attack, Hegland finds out what he has become.

Molly finally moves downtown, but with Sarah and Mateo busy all the time, it's not as fun as she imagined. And she's not about to start hanging with, ew, Rome.

Her new catsitting client offers up her place for a party and Molly takes a shot at being a social butterfly to reconnect with her friends, but it doesn't quite turn out as she planned.

volume.name: Finding Molly: An Adventure In Catsitting

description:
Holy Cow Comics featuring Atomic Bear

Meet the radioactive protector of the forest, Atomic Bear, as he uses his irradiated abilities to stop a twister, meet Napoleon and Nikola Tesla and come to grips with the rampaging Time Chicken!
name: Atomic Bear

description: There are few we can trust in this world when it spins into chaos, but the heart only knows what it wants to pursue. Dreams, ambitions, and people all weave their way inside each other. When trust is established, why wouldn't we be quick to love?

The Marvel Chess Collection is a new bi-weekly series offering the comic fan and chess lover alike the chance to collect a unique chess set, featuring some of the greatest and most loved Marvel characters. The second set in the Marvel Chess Collection features the X-Men.
name: Wolverine [White Knight]

description: The Marvel Chess Collection is a new bi-weekly series offering the comic fan and chess lover alike the chance to collect a unique chess set, featuring some of the greatest and most loved Marvel characters. The second set in the Marvel Chess Collection features the X-Men.
name: Cable [White Pawn]

description: The Marvel Chess Collection is a new bi-weekly series offering the comic fan and chess lover alike the chance to collect a unique chess set, featuring some of the greatest and most loved Marvel characters. The second set in the Marvel Chess Collection features the X-Men.
name: Scalphunter [Black Pawn]

description: The Marvel Chess Collection is a new bi-weekly series offering the comic fan and chess lover alike the chance to collect a unique chess set, featuring some of the greatest and most loved Marvel characters. The second set in the Marvel Chess Collection features the X-Men.
name: Psylocke [White Pawn]

description: The Marvel Chess Collection is a bi-weekly series featuring some of the greatest Marvel characters. The second set in the Marvel Chess Collection features the X-Men. #59 Bastion - (Black Knight) #60 Donald Pierce - (Black Pawn) #61 Nimrod - (Black Rook) #62 ShadowCat - (White Pawn)
name: Donald Pierce [Black Pawn]

description: The Marvel Chess Collection is a bi-weekly series featuring some of the greatest Marvel characters. The second set in the Marvel Chess Collection features the X-Men. #59 Bastion - (Black Knight) #60 Donald Pierce - (Black Pawn) #61 Nimrod - (Black Rook) #62 ShadowCat - (White Pawn)
name: Nimrod [Black Rook]

description:
Collects Year Four of the online comic Ménage à 3

Color cover with b&w interiors

Once all but invisible to women, Gary comics artist finds himself more and more the center of attention, as the efforts of his wing-girl Zii and kiss-trainer Dillon start bearing fruit. But who will win his heart, and his bed? Yuki, his scriptwriter? Kiley, Yuki's therapist? Sonya, his drama-loving first date? Amber, the ex-porn star? Zii? Dillon in a wig? "Three" was only the beginning... get ready for a menage a MORE!

Bonus features include:

  • An all new 5-page, print exclusive, "what-if" bonus story featuring gender-flipped strips!
  • Part 1 of the Senna & Sandra Adventures.
  • 6 new chapter break illustrations, and a new back cover illustration!
name: Round 4

description:
Do the Sprite Thing

What's Mucho Man doing in Ireland?

Who are the Far Darrig?!

What happened to The Gondolier?!!

Who is Dysplastic Man?!!!

Does anyone read these issue description?!!!!
name: Do the Sprite Thing

description:
Two Nancy Drew mysteries- In "Doggone Town," Nancy and Ned investigate the mysterious disappearance of the entire population of a town, and Nancy finds a new pet. In "Sleight of Dan," Nancy solves the mystery of a missing magician's assistant-while avoiding the jaws of a hungry green anaconda.

Note: The digital edition (5/18/2016) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: Doggone Town; Sleight of Dan

description:
Good Morning, Helen --WELCOME TO YOUR NIGHTMARE

Grimalkin's first field mission goes horribly sideways when one of his teammates is killed!

So why is he experiencing the most peace he's had in 30 years?

Where's My Rich Girl?

After the loss of one of The Fog. Revenger, Jenny, and Slim go their separate ways but the torment isn't over... Oh, and there is more violence. I know you like violence.
name: Where's My Rich Girl?

person_credits.name: Charles Forsman
person_credits.role: writer, artist, letterer, colorist, cover, production

description:
Choices!

Startup's desperate quest to rescue her son from Big Shot brings her face to face with the deadly assassin called Chain! Startup's origin arc concludes in this instant classic from Darin Henry (Seinfeld, KC Undercover), Craig Rousseau (Batman Beyond, Harley Quinn), Glenn Whitmore (Superman) and Marshall Dillon. And don't miss a special cameo appearance by The Blue Baron and the Heroes Union!
name: Choices!

description:
The Ever-Squirming Brain

A random act of violence in the street prompts Raymond to remember a grim incident from his past. Meanwhile, as the darkness of the human heart emerges in the present, Raymond finds his strength once again.
name: The Ever-Squirming Brain

description:
Future Lizards

David and Sloth have returned to the future without Tesla, but everything is wrong...
name: Future Lizards

description: A request of the mayor of Terminus leads Toby outside of the metropolis to the Silver Bay. Check out what dark secret lies ahead beyond the last outpost of freedom.

The Millionaire's Fall Part 2

Freed from captivity in New Mexico, Big Money joins Mr. Monopoly in a new business venture where they make sure justice is served for those who can afford it.
name: The Millionaire's Fall Part 2

description:
Searching for Something

In the year 1994, a superhuman attack destroyed much of the city of New York. Many were lost, including major world leaders and costumed heroes gathered together to commemorate the end of the Cold War. During that attack, a shockwave swept the planet and killed every Unique with psionic powers except for one - a young girl named Hope Sage.

Two years later, she woke from a coma into a different world. With so few superheroes left, and after years of economic and social turbulence, she isn't the only one trying to make sense of the changes around her and find a new way forward.
name: Searching For Something

description:
All out war breaks loose in the streets of Westminster, as the Vanguard desperately defend Number 10 against violent mobs and super-powered foes.

Facing impossible odds, can our heroes hold the line until reinforcements arrive?

Find out in VANGUARD - issue eight!

Set against the backdrop of StreamPunk Victorian London in 1856, a plucky young American detective, Cordelia Swift, is the newest addition to Scotland Yard, much to the disgust of her peers and colleagues for both being foreign and a woman. Cordelia is a smart, but naïve detective with everything to prove and prove she must as her first case is to catch a homicidal maniac of monstrous proportions, who is terrorising the innocent people of the East End.
name: Run & Hyde: Part One

description: Adele Leigh Voss was once hailed as a hero. Using her powers for the good of mankind earned her the respect and admiration of the whole world. Unfortunately for ALV times have changed. She is now a wanted woman, hunted and forced into hiding. But, things are never that simple....

volume.name: ALV: The World's Only Super Human

description:
A serial killer has crippled Glass City using fear, for the better part of a year. Killing to a soundtrack, he mysteriously has tapped into the city’s PA systems and radio frequencies; uniting and terrifying the city in the moments of his murders. Hope comes in the form of an anonymous letter with a tip-off to the ‘Throne of God’s’ next killing site. Racing towards the majestic Glass City with shotgun in tow, Detective Drekker is desperate enough to follow this anonymous letter. Then it happens, the speakers of the city crackle to life, and the song begins to play. Boy Zero is an epic noir spanning decades and two separate murder mysteries. The cases are somehow intertwined and Detective Drekker must connect them before the killings begin again. Collects issues 1-7.

Note: The digital edition (5/18/2016) for this volume was released before the print edition.

Pirate Bay

Captain Greyfeather and his pirate seagulls are attacking New York! Can Fable & Co. figure out why they are ramming burning barges into the docks in the harbor, or will the nefarious villains succeed in their plans??! What the heck are their plans for The Carriers and NY?? Find out here! Also, witness the introduction of a dangerous new power player in the underbelly of the city!
name: Pirate Bay

description: A family's yearly visit to grandfather's grave.

Authorities have caught wind that someone is supplying a rogue Japanese admiral with illegal war materials out of 1930's Port of San Francisco. A mysterious group called the New York Committee have given American baseball player Moe Berg and Australian explorer George Hubert Wilkins the mission to uncover the truth behind the rumors.

A robot wanders the desert, lost and alone, with no memory of how he got there. The only answers to the mysteries of his past lie with the mechanical inhabitants of this dusty world -- a civilization of robotic frontiersmen who have modelled their society on pulp western stories. Somewhere among a crazy mechanics, a lost star, the threads and the tumbleweeds, he'll start to find the answers he's looking for. Welcome to the dry lands of Far Out!

Schools Out Forever?

Someone burned down the school, and one teacher is particularly relieved to find himself at a loose end as a result. Join Eric and Dawn as they find themselves drawn into a supernatural plot that can surely only end in fire and death.
name: Schools Out Forever?

description: Jason Karns’ Fukitor is an attack of a different kind: reprinted from the artist’s self-published zine, the book is a 144 page compilation of full color comics that reside uneasily between a straight and satirical response to the violence, xenophobia, and sexual and racial stereotypes found in pop culture.
name: GN

description:
Godsend is a superhero/supernatural story that follows the adventures of Austin Jackson whose life is forever changed when he has a strange encounter on his way to Boston to start his new job.

The time is now. The Templars have a new leader for their terror cells, the Mercurian monks have fallen, the blade of power is missing. When the gates of Hell crack open and the damned swordsmen spill out into the real world leading their legions of Hellspawn, only one thing has a chance of holding them back.

The power of the Godsend.

Austin Jackson was just after a chance to make a new life for himself in the big city. Now he must risk his life, soul, and those of his loved ones in order to live up to the responsibilities thrust upon him.

The time is now and Austin is all that stands between us and Armageddon.

A soldier journeys to another universe to recover a deranged military scientist. He's chosen for the mission for one reason: he's the least likely to go insane. But what he sees on the other side pushes his mind to its limits...and if he breaks, the power mad scientist breaks all of reality with him.

Presenting issues #1 and #2 of the hit TOKYO GHOST by RICK REMENDER and SEAN MURPHY in the ultimate artist’s treatment, as MURPHY’s groundbreaking pages are presented in their original inks at glorious 11x17.

volume.name: Image Giant-Sized Artist's Proof Edition: Tokyo Ghost

description:
Mazzari

A strange object falls in the alien planet of Azhkar, unleashing Mazzari, a warrior in a warpath against slavers who submit the innocent that hopes for salvation!
name: Mazzari

description:
Jon Pay, PI vs, Machine Gun Kelly

Cobb City is a dirty old city run by gangsters, racketeers and other sordid criminals. In this town of broken dreams and back alley deals, only one man has the stones to kick crime in the pants and take names!

That man is JON PAY, P.I.!

In this premiere story Jon takes the night off from "crime-fighting", only to find himself in the middle of an attempted kidnapping. Now it's up to Jon and his former partner, Sgt. Linda O'Meilley of the Cobb City Police department to save the day and a man's life.
name: Jon Pay, PI vs, Machine Gun Kelly

description: Lady Mary Cademus lost both the men she loved in the First Crusade. But now 8 years later one of them, her son Oliver, has returned alive. And he isn't alone.

Hákon awakes among the burning wreckage and mangled corpses of a catastrophic battle waged the previous night. Once believing himself the sole survivor of the assault, he soon finds a most unusual refugee watching him from the wilderness.

In the year 2076, the fate of humanity rests in the hands of 21 young warriors known as THE LOVE PUNKS and THE SATELLITE SISTERS.

Follow them as they blast off from Australia's Pilbara Desert to the far reaches of space on a mission to protect the world from an angry sky god.

Neomad is a joint project between Gestalt Publishing and Big hART, working with children in a remote indigenous community in northwest Western Australia.

Created with the help of over 40 young people in the Ieramugadu (Roebourne) community through a series of workshops in scriptwriting, literacy, Photoshop, filmmaking and sound recording over an 18 month period. Award winning illustrator and interactive designer Sutu spent over 500 hours teaching young students to apply a complex colouring system to more than 600 scenes to create NEOMAD. These young people, aged between 7 and 14, star in the comic as the Love Punks and the Satellite Sisters and assisted with the script and the dialogue.

NEOMAD is set around Murujuga (the Burrup Peninsula), which is home to approximately one million petroglyphs (etched rock art), some of which are over thirty thousand years old. These ancient carvings are markings of food sources, ceremonial sites and spirituality. NEOMAD is one way the thousands of years of cultural heritage associated with Murujuga are now being interpreted using contemporary tools.

Following WW2, the United Nations created the Agency for Super-Normal Affairs, tasked with investigating the "super-normal." Recently the agency has been dismantled and the G-Men are looking for answers. Although, they only have one agent alive to interrogate...

On a Tour of Duty in the Persian Gulf, Lieutenant Steph Connisbee is signed on as the pilot on a top secret mission- Operation: Solomon. During this assignment she will uncover secrets and danger and step into the world of Unseen Shadows before she even knows it...
Interval leads THE RESISTANTS on a daring heist of an armored vehicle carrying precious supplies.

Awesome-Gal

RubberMan is back!

Well, not really! But we'll look into that later.

For now it's really about catching up with all these characters. Starting with Awesome-Gal!

This cover is a tribute to Sara Pichelli's Ms. Marvel (2014) #1, which itself was a homage to the cover of Supergirl #1 by Gary Frank.
name: Awesome-Gal

description:
Outlaw's Fugue

Ingela is a girl on the run from her homeland, stowed away aboard a merchant ship. She narrowly escapes death with the help of the ship's navigator, who is not what he seems. Clever schemes and fierce battles await the both of them in this first issue of Scallywags!
name: Outlaw's Fugue

description: Murder at a famed cabaret! Sherlock Holmes and Watson are called in to investigate a double murder at a cabaret in Paris…a crime that has to kept silent. But Inspector Bodine claims the murder and motive are obvious and Mr. Holmes’ help is not needed. Holmes demonstrates that not everything is as it first appears. With guest characters such as Oscar Wilde and Toulouse L’Autrec, the mystery weaves a tapestry of greed, betrayal and forbidden love. Written by Gary Reed (Deadworld/Saint Germaine/Renfield). Also included are several short stories plus a story from writer/artist Guy Davis (B.P.R.D/The Goon).

volume.name: Sherlock Holmes: Murder at the Cabaret

description:
Somewhere in this great nation of ours is Project Skin Horse, an overworked, underfunded secret agency dedicated to assisting America's nonhuman citizens. The receptionist is a clockwork robot, the project head is a swarm of bees, the field team consists of Sweetheart the talking dog and her faithful zombie Unity, and Dr. Tip Wilkin, the one human staffer, feels he can only do his job properly in high heels.

Volume One covers the first year of the award-winning webcomic, complete with lions, rampages, opera-singing silverfish, and verbally abusive aircraft.
name: Volume One

description:
Stealth, skills and style - the life of Ben Ashodi, AKA The Hand, is one hell of a ride. A talented escape artist and professional thief for hire, The Hand teeters on a precarious high wire, balanced between a career of criminality and a strong sense of morals.

Although when responsibility over his past actions catch up with him, it soon becomes clear there are some things even this master escapologist cannot get away from...

Introducing Super General! The Huntress! Devil Girl! These ladies aren't your typical damsels in distress -- they knock back against the things that go "bump in the night!" Prepare to have your spine tingled and titillated by a giant hairy ape-monster, a ghoul with a taste for exotic dancers, and a group of bank robbers in for a "hell" of a time!

After decades of failing to create the world's first super-heroes, the Powers That Be finally succeed. They didn't expect to create the world's first super-villains instead. Now, under new management, and with five wayward souls, they create one more team to stop them...but not without a contingency plan.

The bear. The zombie. The bullet-proof man. The bee-secreting teen. The telepath. The beginning of a new chapter in human evolution. What could possibly go wrong?

Terminals vol. 1 collects issues #1-6, the entire Terminals saga, from creators Rove and Ryan Ferrier, for the first time in print.
name: Vol. 1

description:
Cold

The TERMINALS saga continues in TERMINALS: BLOODLINES-expanding the rich mythology created by Rove and Ryan Ferrier.

Who was the "flying man" that started it all? See the secret origins of the super-hero program as it dates back to the cold-war. When a group of youth are drafted into the military's special program, an awakening sleeper cell sets off a chain reaction that will change the course of history and human potential as we know it.
name: Cold

description: Special Warlash preview. Warlash: Zombie Mutant Genesis--After a mysterious mutilation death baffles police, Warlash puts himself on the case only to discover evidence of an insidious new threat to the citizens of Pittsburgh; the rise of the Zombie Mutants. Also a preview of the one-shot warlash:Dark City, featuring two tales of exciting battle action. "Enter:the Superior" pitts warlash against a genius foe and his cyborg battle-bot. In "The Generator", Warlash attempts to rescue a girl with special abilities from a diabolical villain.

All This for a Memory?

On an island stronghold, the misfit thief Nod is pursued by the elk-headed Admiral Quo and his army of Sleepwalker Soldiers. She has stolen a an object of great value... a memory.
name: All This For A Memory?

description:
Mystery Man

Ace has defeated the monster that terrorized the good citizens of Century City. A young field report named Abigail Sinclaire is trying to get an exclusive interview with the cities new hero. Her attempts are slowed to a halt when a new mystery man shows up. Who is he and what does he want?
name: Mystery Man

description: The plot thickens as Cordelia and her partner investigate and interrogate a pair of twin scientists based in the East End of London.
name: Run & Hyde: Part Two

description:
Captain Obvious

In this chapter, we meet Juda Al-Jazari; an ex Palestinian soldier who after losing everything he once held dear now only lives for one reason; to be a guardian of the Almier nation.
name: Captain Obvious

description:
"If This Be My Skin" or "Yeah Baby, Clay Baby"

the continuing adventures of ART BALTAZAR's original self published creation...THE CRAY BABY ADVENTURES! Issue 6! The search for the Cray Stick of Joy continues! But our hero may face a Challenge made of living CLAY! Oh No! ALSO! What mysteries lie in the Land of YAHGZ? Introducing the Weezerd and Cray Fu! ALSO, what can come from dreams? Perhaps a life altering event that leads you on the right path! AW YEAH COMICS! is very proud to be representing these adventures after 20 years...AW YEAH!
name: "If This Be My Skin" or "Yeah Baby, Clay Baby"

description: Dan and Joules are stuck between a rock and a hard place. At odds with Max over a hard decision about the Lorkis and and as always low on coffee, will they make it?

The race is on to stop Brandon’s murderous quest for earning penance. As the circle of the detectives and FBI closes in, Brandon is compelled to continue his bloody orgy, regardless of the consequences. The exciting conclusion to the two part Divine Comedy story from writer Matt Nicholls (Collateral) and artist Simon Wright (Zombie Cities).

In Heroes Haven issue 4 Venus grows into a strong little girl trained to fight from her father Mr. Smith, their bond strengthens to hope and unbreakable love of indestructible steel. Smith helps her release her guilt to find joy, until the second most fated day in Venus' life happens that not only changes the course of her life forever, but might prove truth to the rumors of her being the chosen one.
name: The Birth of Venus - The Conclusion

description: After years of over-caffeinated and restless free time, acclaimed artist and writer Nicole J Georges has amassed hundreds of pages of autobiographic comics, lush illustrations of doggies and elephants, and confessional diary entries in her zine Invincible Summer. This volume presents the next four years in the continuing adventures of our intrepid hero and her tumultuous, yet always entertaining life. We're also treated to the usual vegan recipes, priceless moments, friendships, humor, fashion, and heart from this rad Portland lady.
name: Vol. 2

description:
Operation Thunder

With Raven in possession of the Shadowman, Astra and Troy are sent on a mission to retrieve her.
name: Operation Thunder

description: Since he is 3400 hundred years old, Adam Ray can offer some great firsthand insights to his his friend Colin, the museum curator on the artifacts discovered of the cat god Bast. But there are others interested in this find as well: two space aliens Augah and Rushee who have a much greater affinity for cats than for humans. When the three terrorist stooges who are thrown into the mix all hell breaks loose with Adam, Colin and our kitty narrator thrown right in the middle. Zany and wacky antics ensue with a hot heroine and non stop action. Don't miss it!
name: The Avatar of Bast

description: Society reacts to Buck's totally air-tight theory about inanimate rocks attacking the earth! Chaos and hilarity ensue, as Buck decides whether to detonate the C4 explosives he has placed around every rock formation on earth!

Mad Dog prt.4

Rob the werewolf hates Romero the vampire. The feelings are mutual, and Shawn finally gets to learn why. But this new information is getting him no closer to finding peace between the two former friends. When Shawn gets trapped, will these two enemies work together to help their new friend?
name: Mad Dog prt.4

description:
Episode 2: The Gal of Steel

RubberMan is back!

Well, not really! But we'll look into that later.

The story of Ms. Robota starts right here!

description: Come ride along on a dangerous adventure with crime fighting super cars, a mysterious elixir and gun blazing rockabilly babes!

She's like you and me. She's a reader and a dreamer. She has sisters and a mom. She's a little bit unsure about that dress she has to wear to the Big Dance.

Then again, she isn't like us. Living in a castle on the Moon doesn't provide the adventure she craves and she wants nothing more than to do something fun and exciting!

The universe of Doiditos is a reinterpretation of classic cartoon cat and mouse (as Tom and Jerry, Speedy Gonzales, herman & catnip etc..) And inspired by the creativity of Slapstick Comedies of silent movie days. There are no dialogues. The language is visual; the characters use sign language, thought bubbles and can laugh at most, use interjections, (ouch! Ouch!) Or onomatopoeic sounds, to strengthen communication, but can never speak. With this premise are their stories understandable to children of any age (but the target is for 4 - 7 years old). The stories revolve around three characters: Maddog, Madcat and Mamouse .

Madcat and Madmouse while acting as a cat and mouse, are friends. The real clash is between the Maddog representing imagination, Madcat what is rational and Madmouse what is dream. For Maddog all that imagination can conceive, you can perform. It is based on the central theme of the stories. As always when then cat chases mouse, the dog intervenes in history bringing some element of absurdity that detracts from the pursuit and introduces situations nonsense humor.
